org.cooltrainer.xval
Class XVal

java.lang.Object
  org.cooltrainer.xval.XVal

public class XVal
extends java.lang.Object

The XVal class decrypts the 'X' value displayed on the "System Info" screen of the Xbox 360 dashboard. This encrypted string gives information about the security event history of the console.

Since:
2012-06-23
Author:
Nicole Reid

Method Detail

isValidPair

public boolean isValidPair()
Validates a serial number / X value pair. A non-matching serial and X value won't throw an exception in DecryptXVal(String, byte[]) but will return a junk decrypted XVal.

Returns:
true if instantiated serial + xval match, false if not

isClean

public boolean isClean()
Gives quick pass or fail status of a successfully decrypted X value. isValidPair() should be checked first for sanity. Use flags() to get flags if this returns false.

Returns:
True if this X value is clean, false if it is flagged

flags

public java.lang.String flags()
Displays this instance's secdata.bin flags in human-readable form.

secdata.bin flags recorded in the instantiated X value
